This is unfortunately a copy paste of pertinent sections, was easier this way

IN GENERAL
right clicking will give you an option to inspect element, otherwise press F12

CREDIT TO UDACTIY

Google Chrome
right-click on any page element and select Inspect
top-right corner of your browser window and select More Tools > Developer Tools
Command + Option + i (Mac)
Ctrl + Shift + i (Windows/Linux).

Mozilla Firefox
right-click on any page element and select Inspect Element
top-right corner of your browser window and select Developer
Command + Option + i (Mac)
Ctrl + Shift + i (Windows/Linux).

Internet Explorer
developer tools by simply pressing F12

Microsoft Edge
developer tools by simply pressing F12

Safari
right-click on any page element and select Inspect Element
Command + Option + i.

Opera
developer tools. Named Opera Dragonfly
right-clicking in the page and selecting Inspect Element.
Launch Opera Dragonfly with the following keyboard shortcuts:
Command + Option + i (Mac)
Ctrl + Shift + i (Windows/Linux).
